{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the Carer\u2019s Allowance to equal 35 hours at minimum wage",
        "additional_details": "By being paid minimum wage, this could increase to around \u00a31700 per month if they are paid the minimum wage.\r\n \r\nWe believe unpaid carers save the Treasury billions of pounds, many are paid around \u00a32.50 an hour, which we feel is an insulting amount and only continues because many carers carry out social care out of love.",
        "background": "I want the Government to appreciate unpaid carers who can\u2019t work and to increase the Carer\u2019s Allowance so it equals the minimum wage. Many unpaid carers are only paid around \u00a3333 a month for a minimum 140 hours care every 4 weeks, which works out around \u00a32.50 an hour.",
